<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[136,1452,1847,2090]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Erect or ascending, often forming large rich-branched clumps, to 
<quantity box="[901,974,1847,1874]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="cm" value="50.0">50 cm</quantity>
tall. Shoots homophyllous, equally thick throughout, 
<quantity box="[275,398,1884,1910]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="14.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="10.0">10–18 mm</quantity>
in diam. incl. leaves. Stems excl. leaves 
<quantity box="[871,966,1883,1910]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6 mm</quantity>
thick at the base, ridged by decurrent leaf bases (dried). Leaves uniform throughout, borne in alternating, distant to crowded whorls of 5–6, these (2–) 
<quantity box="[1358,1452,1919,1946]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6 mm</quantity>
apart, wide-spreading or ascending to sharply reflexed, usually strongly recurved, lanceolate, usually short-acute, 5–8 
<emphasis box="[185,204,1992,2017]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">×</emphasis>
<quantity box="[211,327,1992,2018]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="1.6" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.2">1.2–2 mm</quantity>
, usually adaxially convex and shining with obscure to prominent vein, abaxially irregularly concave (dried) dull, coriaceous, with obscure to somewhat prominent vein, with flat to slightly revolute, sparsely toothed to nearly entire margins. Leaf bases prominently decurrent; sporangia 
<quantity box="[894,1008,2063,2090]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" unit="mm" value="1.75" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.5">1.5–2 mm</quantity>
wide.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
